{"word":"G4043 - περιπατέω - peripatéō - per-ee-pat-eh'-o - Go","slug":"G4043","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">περιπατέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>peripatéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>per-ee-pat-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Go"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C0;&#x03B5;&#x03C1;&#x03B9;&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - peripateo&#x0304;</b> - <i>per-ee-pat-eh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G4012\">G4012</a> and <a href=\"#/G3961\">G3961</a>; to <i>tread</i> all <i>around</i>, that is, <i>walk</i> at large (especially as proof of ability); figuratively to <i>live</i>, <i>deport oneself</i>, <i>follow</i> (as a companion or votary): - go, be occupied with, walk (about)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1704\">G1704</a>, <a href=\"#/G2662\">G2662</a>, <a href=\"#/G3961\">G3961</a>"}]}